rComments: I had professor Kosteski for two courses in my final year. CSC326(programming languages) and ECE334. In both courses he was an amazing prof, who deeply cares about his students. He is very approachable and willing to discuss issues after class. You can tell he puts a lot of efforts in to lecture. Great Professor.

He Doesn't understand operating system at all. Compare to Yuan Ding and Goel. He is teaching a completely different course which is good for high school students. If you dont want to fail job interviews with is questions, drop his course!
Fantastic prof, explains things really well. Also kinda nerdy cute
He is really caring. He cares about students' thoughts. And his lectures are interesting, i really enjoy the courses.
Interesting OS. Interesting prof. Definitely want to take his classes again.

He makes sure students understand the material and does a lot of examples in class. Tome was also understanding when the midterm average was low and removed a question to boost everyone's grades. He is a bit boring though.
